  "E": {
    "description": "A collimated thermal (2.5 meV) or cold (1 meV) neutron beam traverses the sample; attenuation is governed by mu_n(r, lambda) = Sigma_tot = n * sigma_tot (Sigma ~ 1/E for thermal). Neutrons excel at light elements (H, Li, B, Cd) hidden behind heavy metals (Pb, W) where X-rays fail. Scintillator (LiF/ZnS:Ag) + CCD or MCP+Timepix records transmitted beam.",
